<figureCitation box="[151,286,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[297,395,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">200–203</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1650,2037]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1650,1676]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Description.</emphasis>
Pale brown, yellowish or greenish, often with variable dark pattern on head, pro-, and mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,1687,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Figs. 46–47</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with distinct median carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1650,2037]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[495,511,1722,1736]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">nd</superScript>
tergite in male long, narrow triangular, separated by oval notch (
<figureCitation box="[1239,1338,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 201</figureCitation>
). Sternal apodemes of similar shape, but wider and shorter, separated by wide notch (
<figureCitation box="[977,1073,1759,1785]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 202</figureCitation>
). Penis stem in side view narrow, evenly bent at almost right angle (
<figureCitation box="[523,619,1795,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 200</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[651,667,1794,1808]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 2–3 preapical teeth each (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1351,1795,1821]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 203</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
